Bayesian Neural Networks¶

This notebook uses the BayesianNetworks module, which contains the actual implementation of both classic neural networks (trained using gradient descent) and bayesian ones (trained using MCMC). The source code of the module can be found in the same folder as the notebook.

Under test/ folder you can find proof-of-concept training and prediction procedures for the following datasets:

  • the sanity check presented in the course, re-learning a neural network
  • XOR classification
  • two-moons classification
  • Iris
  • N blobs classification

In this notebook we won't look at all the approaches, instead we will show results only for the interesting parts.

Correctness validation: XOR classification¶

XOR classification is a non-linear classification problem and it is frequently used as a sanity check for machine learning algorithms. We will use it to ensure that our implementations are in fact correct.

In [70]:
Random.seed!(SEED)

dataset_size = 5000
test_split_size = trunc(Int, dataset_size * 0.1)

epochs = 500
batch_size = 256

X, y = BayesianNetworks.Xor.make_dataset(dataset_size)
val_X, val_y = BayesianNetworks.Xor.make_dataset(test_split_size)
test_X, test_y = BayesianNetworks.Xor.make_dataset(test_split_size)

Neural network training using mini-batch Gradient Descent¶

In [73]:
network = BayesianNetworks.Xor.make_network()
network, losses, val_losses = BayesianNetworks.train_model_using_gd(
    network, X, y_onehot, 
    val_X=val_X, val_y=val_y_onehot,
    batchsize=batch_size, epochs=epochs
)
y_pred = BayesianNetworks.predict(network, X, BayesianNetworks.Xor.labels)
train_acc = BayesianNetworks.accuracy(y, y_pred)
y_pred = BayesianNetworks.predict(network, val_X, BayesianNetworks.Xor.labels)
val_acc = BayesianNetworks.accuracy(val_y, y_pred)
y_pred = BayesianNetworks.predict(network, test_X, BayesianNetworks.Xor.labels)
test_acc = BayesianNetworks.accuracy(test_y, y_pred)

train_acc, val_acc, test_acc

Bayesian neural network training using mini-batch Metropolis-Hastings¶

In [78]:
network = BayesianNetworks.Xor.make_network()
networks, losses, val_losses, accuracies = BayesianNetworks.infer_models_using_mcmc(
    network, X, y, BayesianNetworks.Xor.labels;
    val_X=val_X, val_y=val_y,
    burnin_epochs=epochs, inference_epochs=500, batchsize=batch_size,
    ascending_select=true,
)
mean_y_pred = [BayesianNetworks.predict(network, X, BayesianNetworks.Xor.labels) for network in networks]
mean_y_pred = round.(mean(mean_y_pred))
train_acc = BayesianNetworks.accuracy(y, mean_y_pred)
mean_y_pred = [BayesianNetworks.predict(network, val_X, BayesianNetworks.Xor.labels) for network in networks]
mean_y_pred = round.(mean(mean_y_pred))
val_acc = BayesianNetworks.accuracy(val_y, mean_y_pred)
mean_y_pred = [BayesianNetworks.predict(network, test_X, BayesianNetworks.Xor.labels) for network in networks]
mean_y_pred = round.(mean(mean_y_pred))
test_acc = BayesianNetworks.accuracy(test_y, mean_y_pred)

train_acc, val_acc, test_acc
